30/07/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Four Bosnian Serbs -- Zeljko Mejakic, Momcilo Gruban, Dusan Knezevic and Dragan Fustar -- pleaded not guilty to charges of crimes against humanity, during their appearance before the BiH Court on Friday (28 July). The four are accused of crimes committed against prisoners at the Omarska and Keraterm camp in the Prijedor area in 1992. This was the third case handed over from the UN tribunal to the BiH judiciary. (RTRS, Srna, NTV Hayat - 28/07/06)
